-- Kuwaiti telecom operator Zain signs $250 mln Islamic loan
-- By Matt Smith in Dubai
-- Wed Apr 02, 2014 07:01AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, April 2 (Reuters) - Kuwait's Zain <ZAIN.KW> has secured a $250 million four-year Islamic loan from a syndicate of three Gulf banks, the telecommunications operator said on Wednesday.

Zain, which operates in eight countries in the Middle East and Africa, has signed the Murabaha sharia-compliant cost-plus-profit facility with lead lender Boubyan Bank <BOUK.KW>, plus Kuwait International Bank <KIBK.KW> and Qatar Islamic Bank <QISB.QA>.